### Install instructions for CMake-based build ###

Linux/X11:

    - Install CMake 2.8.9+ and add bin to PATH
    - Install Qt5 and add bin to PATH
    
    - If using a package manager such as Debian package management,
      install the following packages (sudo apt-get install <PACKAGE>):
    -- g++
    -- libdrm-dev
    -- libgl1-mesa-dev
    -- libxi-dev
    -- libxmu-dev
    - (this list may not include all needed packages)
    
    ./configure
    make

    - If QAvimator fails to run due to missing libraries,
      then try adding Qt's lib directory to LD_LIBRARY_PATH

OS X:

    - Install CMake 2.8.9+ and add bin to PATH
    - Install Qt5 and add bin to PATH
    - Install XCode and its command line tools
    
    ./configure
    make

Windows:
    
    - Install CMake 2.8.9+ and add bin to PATH
    - Install Qt5 and add bin to PATH
    - Install MinGW and add bin to PATH (some Qt5 installations come with MinGW)
    
    configure
    make
